<content>From: filecheck@curriki.org
To: $email
Subject: Curriki Resource Improvement Request - $assettitle

Dear Curriki Member $membername,

Thank you for creating a learning resource, $assettitle, in Curriki.

Our preliminary file check found that one of the following is true for this resource:

 - You created a resource from a template or starting building a curriculum, but you haven't developed content in it.
 - You created a resource to test the system or begin a draft, but it is mostly incomplete.
 - Your resource is a broken link or file.
 - Your resources are without immediate educational value for the instructional context.

Due to this issue, your resource has been given a 'Private' setting under Access Privileges; other members of the Curriki community will not be able to view or access this resource.

The Curriki repository offers free learning resources to a global education and learning community; making search results useful and resources valuable is the responsibility of members.

It would be great if you could return and update your resource, offering something of real value for the global education community! Here's how to proceed:

1.    Go to the Curriki site (http://www.curriki.org) and log in.
2.    Use the left menu to go to "My Contributions" under the "My Curriki" heading.
3.    Find the resource you wish to update and click "Edit" from the options on the right. Your resource will open in the Currikulum Builder in a new browser window or tab.
4.    In the Currikulum Builder, click the "Edit" tab to change content in your resource, or the 'Information' tab to update settings.
5.    Once you have completed your revisions and your resource is ready for sharing with others who visit Curriki, click "Public" or "Protected" under Access Privileges on the Information tab.

If you would like more information regarding Curriki's content screening process, or if you would like to discuss this particular submission, please email filecheck@curriki.org.</content>
